#2758
Prisoner's Cell~
Opening the rusty, squeaky door, you find yourself in what closely
resembles a hole in the ground.  In fact, many of the piles of dirt have not
been removed from the cell.  No light at all reaches this room, and the only
source of light is that from your own torch.  Looking around the small cell,
you see groups of nearly naked individuals huddled together for warmth, or
perhaps fear.  They do not seem to notice you, and their blank eyes gaze
forward uncaring.  Strange marks mar their bodies; marks that appear as two
small punctures, usually located near the major arteries.  The only exit
from this cell is the one you entered through, yet the prisoners show no
sign of wanting to leave.
